			<h1>Seattle Vipassana Hall</h1>
			<div class="contentStory spacedParas">
				<div class="inlineRight"><img border="0" src="../Images/SVH/SeattleVipassana.jpg" width="250px" alt="Seattle Vipassana Hall" align="middle"/></div> 
					<p>The Seattle Vipassana Hall serves the old students of S.N. Goenka in the Seattle area by providing opportunities for individual drop-in meditation, scheduled group sittings, one-day courses, youth courses, Vipassana outreach events, and trust and committee meetings. The hall is under the direction  of the NW Vipassana Center (Dhamma Ku&ntilde;ja), and is staffed and supported by grateful old students on a volunteer basis.</p>
					<p>All meditation events are only for old students. Old students are those who have completed a 10-day Vipassana course with S.N. Goenka or his assistant teachers.</p>
				</div>
                <br />
				<!-- schedule -->
        	   	<h2>Schedule of Group Sittings &amp; One-Day Courses </h2>
                <p class="bottomPad">For additional information on One-Day Courses <a href="SeattleVipassana.OneDay.html">please see here</a>.</p>
				<div> 
					<a name="sched"></a>
